Roland Duchâtelet, owner of Standard Liège, warns that club will breakaway from the Belgian Pro League and join France's Ligue 1 if a new Belgian–Dutch league is not created. (The International News)Scottish cyclist Sir Chris Hoy announces his retirement from track cycling. (BBC)In synchronized skating, Team Unique of Finland wins the 2013 World Championships, with NEXXICE of Canada placing second and Haydenettes of the USA third. (U.S. Figure Skating)